AGI - It was born in Palestine but then, because of the conflict, it was literally "abandoned" in the care. Today E.H., a child of just 13 months, suffering from a very serious chronic heart disease and obstructive hydrocephalus, can normally live thanks to a series of life-saving interventions carried out at the Gaslini Hospital in Genoa> and an international humanitarian mission. "This child won a ticket to the lottery of life - says Raffaele Spiazzi, health director of the pediatric hospital - He would surely have died if he had not arrived here." To get her to Gaslini, a mission that involved the Farnesina, the Ministry of Health and Defense: on 11 March the flight and the Air Force, last 3 April the operation. "One joint and international effort: varcare <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-09/biden-stop-consegne-israele-rafah-26324062/"> the border of Rafah</a> is, as we know, very complex - explained the primary of the newborn intensive therapy and Pediatrica of the Gaslini. A difficult journey, with great risk of desaturation: it was necessary to be prepared for any type of criticality. The baby could die in flight. In the aircraft they traveled mothers with children who risk their lives, people for which planes do not mean holiday and leisure but horror and death. Italy took charge of chronic patients who do not have the opportunity to be treated on site".
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The small has been reconstructed a heart "new of mint", > with a definitive radical correction of cardiopathy, which will give it a normal life, then the neuroendoscopic treatment of hydrocephalus, under the guidance of Dr. Gianluca Piatelli. Arrived in desperate conditions, with black hands, now smiles and touches everything curious and alive again. Her young mother, who left with her, always stayed next to her. He will remain for a few weeks: impossible to return to Palestine. "We were one of the rings of this virtuous chain," continued Roberto Formigari, head of the cardiological team. The child now has a four-room heart and an excellent biventricular function, 100% saturation, without residual defects. From the beginning of the conflict 34 children were followed by the Gaslini Institute: have arrived small patients with burns, mutilation, with painless lesions: more than 40% of the population of Gaza is in the 0-14 range and are they, according to humanitarian organizations, to pay the highest cost of the conflict.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"The intervention was very complex > it is necessary to unifocalize the pulmonary artery, to reconstruct a pulmonary bifurcation, to tunnel the left ventricle to the aorta and to replenish the continuity between heart and pulmonary bifurcation through a valve from human donor that we have identified in Barcelona - it has explained the cardio surgeon Guido Michielon, at the head of the unit of Cardiosurgery - Genoasplon has concluded some time".
